    en: "A private parking lot owner — a store, restaurant, or apartment complex — can have a vehicle towed when the vehicle is parked in violation of clearly posted rules. But the lot has to post visible tow-away signs at every entrance, the tow has to be requested by the lot owner (not picked up by a roaming tow truck), and the tow and storage charges have to be reasonable. The main statutes are Vehicle and Traffic Law 1224 and General Business Law 399-aa. A driver whose car was towed has the right to know where the car is, to retrieve personal belongings, and to dispute an improper tow."
